name: MavensMate-Desktop
description: Packaged desktop app for MavensMate server

releases.name: v0.0.11-beta.6
releases.body:
## Heads up: this is a beta release!!
- If you do not want to be a beta tester, do not download this release

### Known Issues
- Streaming debug logs are currently not operational on v37.0 of the Salesforce API. Use 36.0 if you require debug logs.

### Changelog
- resolves EPERM issue when running real-time antivirus (windows)
- set 100mb as max file size for MavensMate logs
- execute-soql command now places response in soql directory in the project
- flush-soql command clears project soql directory
- adds zoom in/out menu items to windows/linux

releases.body:
## Heads up: this is a beta release!!

releases.name: v0.0.11-beta.4
releases.body:
## Heads up: this is a beta release!!
- If you do not want to be a beta tester, do not download this release

### Known Issues
- Streaming debug logs are currently not operational on v37.0 of the Salesforce API. Use 36.0 if you require debug logs.

### Changelog
- adds browser back/forward/reload controls to the UI when navigating Salesforce OAuth pages
- changes method for extracting Metadata API responses from Salesforce, which aims to resolve https://github.com/joeferraro/MavensMate/issues/720
- adds mm_legacy_unzip setting to enable users to fallback to the old method of unzipping in case they encounter issues

releases.name: v0.0.11-beta.3
releases.body:
## Heads up: this is a beta release!!
- If you do not want to be a beta tester, do not download this release

### Known Issues
- Some Windows users are experiencing [`ENOENT: no such file or directory`](https://github.com/joeferraro/MavensMate/issues/720) when trying to compile/refresh. This is happening when MavensMate is attempting to unzip files returned from the Salesforce Metadata API. There is a separate branch dedicated to resolving this issue.
- Streaming debug logs are currently not operational on v37.0 of the Salesforce API. Use 36.0 if you require debug logs.

### Changelog
- resolves issue preventing oauth to sandboxes
- left menu salesforce item now displays api usage on click
- adds mm_polling_interval setting for users hitting api limits
- properly handles "end-user denied authorization" exception during oauth
- makes deploy timeout longer, makes it relative to mm_timeout config
- updates legacy config/.debug on project instantiation
- ensures project names do not include leading/trailing whitespace to avoid potential path issues
- fixes issue where failing test information was not scrollable
- adds `MavensMate-Desktop-Version` header for plugins

releases.name: v0.0.11-beta.2
releases.body:
## Heads up: this is a beta release!!
- If you do not want to be a beta tester, do not download this release
- This is the first official beta for Desktop that uses the Lightning Design System and OAuth

### Changelog
- Completely new UI driven by Lightning Design System
- MavensMate now uses OAuth (instead of username/password flow). This means that existing projects will prompt for re-authentication.
- View Manager allows you to push long-running processes to the background and see their statuses while doing other work
- New Project Home screen with common actions
- Other common actions now available in left-hand menu
- Adds support for upcoming Visual Studio Code plugin
- Laundry list of bug fixes

releases.name: v0.0.10
releases.body:
- Resolves issue where unescaped content in the edit project UI was breaking the page
- Fixes regression where refreshing a single metadata type overwrote the project package.xml
- Changes the way projects are cleaned/refreshed/edited to avoid EPERM issues, especially in windows, when attempting to delete non-empty directories. This also resolves the issue where .svn and .git directories were being wiped out during cleans and edits.
- Resolves issue where unselected metadata in package.xml would display as selected in project tree
- Catches bad settings store and reverts to default settings in those cases
- Updated error message when editor path is not found
- Resolves issue where custom metadata templates were displayed during selection, but not merged during creation
- Removes functionality that autoruns Apex unit tests when opening the test runner UI from the editor for UX reasons. Will re-visit.
- Adds "check for updates" menu item which directs user to /releases
- Resolves issue where if user had pulled project from git, the local store, at times, was not up-to-date with the contents of the src directory, which had multiple side effects inc`luding delayed compile times. Missing local store entry is now caught properly and prompts user to ensure their project's subscription is up-to-date and to clean the project to retrieve the latest server metadata
- Resolves issue where user running the sync with server command without a valid local store caused an unhandled exception
- Resolves issue where MavensMate was not respecting local template configuration
- Resolves issue where Sublime Text was not refreshing the folder tree after operations like clean-project, refresh-metadata, and edit-project, which left an empty src folder in Sublime Text, even though the project metadata existed on the disk
- Resolves issue where Custom Object asterisk in package.xml was not retrieving both custom and standard objects
- Removes search layouts from list of known metadata because they cannot be retrieved explicitly

releases.body:
- Resolves issue where MavensMate was not respecting local template configuration

releases.name: v0.0.9
releases.body:
- MavensMate.app is now properly signed on OSX
- MavensMate-app min width is now slightly smaller
- MavensMate-app default window size is now slightly smaller by default
- Introduces streamlined compilation endpoint for Apex/VF metadata, which cuts out Metadata API calls in an attempt to significantly reduce compilation times on servers where the Metadata API is a bottleneck
- Introduces `mm_legacy_compile` global setting to allow users to turn off the above compilation method in case it uncovers unintended side effects
- Resolves issue where certain very large mavensmate projects were receiving `Error: Request Entity Too Large: head` when running Apex unit tests
- Tweaks metadata indexing to better handle "exotic" metadata types listed in package.xml
- Preselects and runs test automatically if test class passed to run-test command via Sublime Text
- Fixes typo in mm_workspace global settings example, makes example more clear
- Normalizes MavensMateFile paths to reduce situations where bad paths were causing command failures
- Removes the Linux exclusion from keychain to re-enable keychain functionality for Linux users
- Resolves issue where compilation of non Apex Class metadata was still attempting to index symbol tables, costing unnecessary API hits
- Resolves issue where expired security token was causing project initialization issues
- Minor UI tweaks

releases.name: v0.0.8
releases.body:
- resolves issue with indexing certain metadata types like workflow rules and sharing rules
- windows installer now gives the option of doing a portable install
- resolves issue where deployment connections were unable to authenticate properly for certain org types
- better handles situation where windows users did not have cscript on their path, preventing unzipping

- resolves issue where Windows users were being asked to confirm during refreshes
